<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
The protologue for 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. crassifolius" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="crassifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">A. crassifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cites a specimen from Martaban in Myanmar. In addition, a regional checklist (
<bibRefCitation author="Kress, WJ" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 590" refId="B11" refString="Kress, WJ, DeFilipps, RA, Farr, E, Kyi, DYY, 2003. A checklist of the trees, shrubs, herbs, and climbers of Myanmar. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 45: 1 - 590" title="A checklist of the trees, shrubs, herbs, and climbers of Myanmar." volume="45" year="2003">Kress et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
) and a forest flora (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.52413" author="Kurz, S" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" refId="B12" refString="Kurz, S, 1877. Forest flora of British Burma. Vol. 1. Office of the Superintendent of Government Printing, Calcutta. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.52413" title="Forest flora of British Burma. Vol. 1. Office of the Superintendent of Government Printing, Calcutta." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.52413" year="1877">Kurz 1877</bibRefCitation>
) indicate the presence of this species in Tenasserim (Taninthayi), Myanmar. However, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/njb.00689" author="Turner, IM" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" pagination="257 - 299" refId="B17" refString="Turner, IM, 2015. A conspectus of Indo-Burmese Annonaceae. Nordic Journal of Botany 33 (3): 257 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/njb.00689" title="A conspectus of Indo-Burmese Annonaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/njb.00689" volume="33" year="2015">Turner (2015)</bibRefCitation>
was unable to trace the syntype or any other specimen of this species from Myanmar; our attempts to trace those specimens were likewise in vain. The occurrence of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. crassifolius" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="crassifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">A. crassifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Myanmar therefore requires future verification. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Artabotrys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Artabotrys crassifolius" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crassifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Artabotrys crassifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species in Thailand as its young twigs, flower pedicels and lower surface of sepals have a dense covering of long appressed hairs that is visible with the naked eye. In Thailand, this species is currently known from a single gathering from Trang, which exhibits the unique indumentum mentioned earlier and has monocarps with shape and size matching 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. crassifolius" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="crassifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">A. crassifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimens of this gathering were previously filed as ' 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Artabotrys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Artabotrys" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Artabotrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="indet’">indet'</normalizedToken>
and only recently identified for the Flora of Thailand project. Outside of Thailand, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. crassifolius" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="crassifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">A. crassifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in Peninsular Malaysia but restricted to the Central Catchment Nature Reserve and Bukit Timah Nature Reserve in Singapore.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
